The ~/.bash_profile is executed when you login using console or remotely using SSH.
Edit the file: vi ~/.bash_profile
Command: export PATH=${PATH}:${HOME}/bin
   Here, {HOME} is the directory path where the required software is installed

Example:    git=/dir/path/to/git
            kubectl=/dir/path/to/kubectl
            export PATH=${PATH}:${git}/bin:${kubectl}/bin